I am in no way an expert in community management or how to build a product, but as someone who has a deep love for the value of Twitter, it is baffling to me how little has changed over its lifetime. I get that scale is hard. I get that simplicity is good. But it's malpractice.

"People you should follow" is a joke. Why aren't there better tools for managing who I follow? Why isn't there a tool to unfollow people who haven't tweeted in X years? Or whose tweets I've never liked? Why is the reporting system a black box? Why can't we elect moderators? https://t.co/JYMtee6V96

I know that ideas are cheap and execution is hard, but I believe in you guys. Beyond the abuse issues, there are basic UX wins you could make. Why can't people charge their followers per month like a newsletter or patreon? Why can't I tweak & customize my own timeline algorithm? https://t.co/eUNh3xJbXi
